One person died while three other sustained serious injuries after a lorry lost control and crashed into a shop in Tawa, Makueni county on Sunday. The lorry, which was traveling from Masii in Machakos, appeared to have brake failure on a slope near Tawa, witnesses told Citizen Digital. The driver of the ill-fated lorry, his turn boy, and two women who were walking were among those injured. One of the ladies succumbed to her injuries while receiving treatment at the Tawa Hospital on Sunday. According to Makueni County police chief Joseph Ole Napeiyan, who confirmed the incident, the lorry driver was taken to the Makueni Referral Hospital for specialized treatment. The two others are receiving medical care at the Tawa Hospital as investigations into the accidentâ€™s cause continue. Video Of The Day: Former sports CS Hassan Wario convicted over Rio games scam